reviewtext: This is from a Fluke 75III meterSignal induction/crosstalk between conductors = unmeasureable.Signal loss on 2 data wires = ~.05 Ohms from pin to pin.Signal loss on 2 (distinct) ground wires = ~.06 Ohms, pin to pin.Solder joints (while not entriely pretty) are not cold/flawed in any visible way.The individual ground shielding at one end of my cable was close to contact, but was not touching.Overall i'm pleased...
